                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/20.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my November 17. I have been informed by several Americans that they
                    have been ordered to report to the Governor, to pay several thousand dollars
                    each. On the basis of Department’s instructions to Consular service in Mexico, I
                    shall earnestly protest against Americans being called to pay forced loans.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
